<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>This is the shocking moment a woman videos herself hanging out of a car travelling at '110mph' on the M25 with the caption 'I'm going to end up dead' before falling out onto the M25.</p>

<p>Video posted on social media site Snapchat shows the unnamed woman performing the extremely dangerous stunt near Clacket Lane Services in Surrey. </p>

<p>The social media post is captioned 'I need to stop doing this. 110mph imma (sic) end up dead.'  </p>

<p>She then fell out of the vehicle at 1.30am on Saturday, between the service station and junction six of the M25.</p>

<p>Surrey Police officers Tweeted about the accident.</p>

<p>The woman was not badly hurt but the police added that it was lucky 'she wasn't seriously injured or killed'.</p>

<p>Police have released a picture of the inside of the car which the woman fell out of during the incident in the early hours of Saturday</p>

